Museum of Modern History of Korea
address: 1652-10 Beopheung-ri, Tanhyeon-myeon, Paju-si, Gyeonggi-do, South Korea
description: In order not to forget the past, in 2005, more than 70,000 various visual cultural relics collected over the past 30 years were transferred to Heili Village. The Korea Museum of Modern and Contemporary History, which exudes a strong sense of the past from the entrance, consists of one basement floor and three floors above ground.

The Biological Resources Museum is located in Incheon, South Korea, and is an important research institution for biological resources in Korea. There are exhibition rooms, ecological halls, wild gardens, wild stages and other areas in the museum, which collect more than 1,000 species of creatures and native biological specimens, showing the changing process of mountains, forests and lakes. In addition, the lawn area in front of the pavilion is also very popular, and many people go on outings here.
